problem:
Let $ABCD$ be a parallelogram. We have that $M$ is the midpoint of $AB$ and $N$ is the midpoint of $BC.$ The segments $DM$ and $DN$ intersect $AC$ at $P$ and $Q$, respectively. If $AC = 17817,$ what is $QA$? [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, pM, pN, O, P, Q;
A = (25, 0) * dir(-20);
B = (15, 0) * dir(60);
C = (25, 0) * dir(160);
D = (15, 0) * dir(-120);
pM = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * B;
pN = 0.5 * B + 0.5 * C;
O = 0.25 * A + 0.25 * B + 0.25 * C + 0.25 * D;
P = 0.33 * C + 0.67 * A;
Q = 0.67 * C + 0.33 * A;
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);
draw(A--C);
draw(pM--D);
draw(pN--D);
label("$A$", A, S);
label("$B$", B, NE);
label("$C$", C, NW);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$M$", pM, NE);
label("$N$", pN, NW);
label("$P$", P, N);
label("$Q$", Q, NE);
[/asy]
